
// This Hyperlambda code constructs a SQL statement to add a foreign key constraint to a table. It uses the [set-value] slot to set the value of the [.tail] node by concatenating various strings and values retrieved from the [.arguments] node. The [strings.concat] slot combines static strings with dynamic values such as [tableName], [columnName], [foreignTable], and [foreignField] to form the complete SQL command.
set-value:x:@.tail
   strings.concat
      .:"alter table "
      get-value:x:@.arguments/*/tableName
      .:" add foreign key ("
      get-value:x:@.arguments/*/columnName
      .:") references "
      get-value:x:@.arguments/*/foreignTable
      .:(
      get-value:x:@.arguments/*/foreignField
      .:)
